# Plan: Optimize `issue list` with `collapse` parameter

## Summary

The Sentry web UI optimizes issue list loading by sending `collapse=stats,unhandled` to `/organizations/{org}/issues/`, skipping expensive Snuba/ClickHouse queries. The CLI currently requests everything, adding **200-500ms per API request**. This change adds `collapse` parameter support to skip unused data.

**Note:** The Discover endpoint (`/events/?dataset=errors`) cannot replace `issue list` — issues are aggregations above events that only the Issues API provides. The performance win comes from the `collapse` query parameter on the same endpoint.

## What the CLI actually uses from SentryIssue

| Column | Field | Source |
|--------|-------|--------|
| SHORT ID | `shortId` | base (PG) |
| ISSUE | `title`, `metadata` | base (PG) |
| SEEN | `lastSeen` | base (PG) |
| AGE | `firstSeen` | base (PG) |
| TREND | `stats` (sparkline) + `substatus` | **stats (Snuba)** + base |
| EVENTS | `count` | base (period-scoped, NOT `lifetime`) |
| USERS | `userCount` | base (period-scoped, NOT `lifetime`) |
| TRIAGE | `priority`, `seerFixabilityScore` | base (PG) |

**Never consumed by issue list:** `lifetime`, `filtered`, `unhandled` (isUnhandled only used in `issue view`)

## Collapse Strategy

| Scenario | collapse | groupStatsPeriod | Savings |
|----------|----------|-----------------|---------|
| Human, wide terminal (≥100 cols) | `[filtered, lifetime, unhandled]` | `"auto"` | ~200ms |
| Human, narrow terminal (<100 cols) | `[filtered, lifetime, unhandled, stats]` | omitted | ~400ms |
| Human, non-TTY (piped) | `[filtered, lifetime, unhandled, stats]` | omitted | ~400ms |
| JSON (`--json`) | `[filtered, lifetime, unhandled, stats]` | omitted | ~400ms |

Stats are only needed for the TREND sparkline column, shown when `process.stdout.columns >= 100`.

